Here's how to handle each scenario with MSTest:

### 1. Windows-only tests

```csharp
[TestMethod]
[OSCondition(OperatingSystems.Windows)]  // custom helper, or:
public void Registry_ReadsValue()
{
    if (!OperatingSystem.IsWindows())
    {
        Assert.Inconclusive("Requires Windows.");
        return;
    }
    // ... registry code
}
```

### 2. Skip in CI (requires local GPU)

```csharp
[TestMethod]
public void Render_UsesGpu()
{
    if (Environment.GetEnvironmentVariable("CI") is not null)
    {
        Assert.Inconclusive("Skipped in CI — requires local GPU.");
        return;
    }
    // ... GPU test
}
```

Or use a **custom attribute** for reuse:

```csharp
[AttributeUsage(AttributeTargets.Method, AllowMultiple = false)]
public class SkipInCIAttribute : Attribute { }

// In your base class or test initializer:
[TestInitialize]
public void CheckSkipConditions()
{
    var method = GetType().GetMethod(TestContext.TestName!);
    if (method?.GetCustomAttribute<SkipInCIAttribute>() is not null
        && Environment.GetEnvironmentVariable("CI") is not null)
    {
        Assert.Inconclusive("Skipped in CI.");
    }
}
```

### 3. Flaky external API — retry pattern

```csharp
[TestMethod]
[DataRow(1)]
[DataRow(2)]
[DataRow(3)] // poor-man's retry via data rows — but better:
public void Weather_ReturnsForecast()
{
    Exception? last = null;
    for (int attempt = 0; attempt < 3; attempt++)
    {
        try
        {
            var result = WeatherClient.GetForecast();
            Assert.IsNotNull(result);
            return; // success
        }
        catch (HttpRequestException ex)
        {
            last = ex;
            Thread.Sleep(1000 * (attempt + 1)); // backoff
        }
    }
    Assert.Fail($"Flaky after 3 retries: {last?.Message}");
}
```

> **Better long-term:** mock the weather API in unit tests and move the real call to an integration test suite with its own retry/tolerance policy.

### 4. Cleanup even on failure — use `[TestCleanup]`

```csharp
[TestClass]
public class FileTests
{
    private readonly List<string> _tempFiles = new();

    [TestMethod]
    public void Process_WritesToTempFile()
    {
        var path = Path.GetTempFileName();
        _tempFiles.Add(path);

        File.WriteAllText(path, "data");
        var result = Processor.Run(path);
        Assert.IsTrue(result.Success);
    }

    [TestCleanup]  // runs after EVERY test, even on failure
    public void Cleanup()
    {
        foreach (var f in _tempFiles)
        {
            try { File.Delete(f); } catch { /* best-effort */ }
        }
        _tempFiles.Clear();
    }
}
```

### Summary

| Scenario | Mechanism |
|---|---|
| OS-specific | `Assert.Inconclusive()` + runtime check |
| Skip in CI | Check `CI` env var; custom attribute for reuse |
| Flaky API | Retry loop with backoff (or mock it) |
| Cleanup on failure | `[TestCleanup]` — guaranteed to run |

`Assert.Inconclusive` is the key MSTest tool for conditional skips — it marks the test as "not run" rather than pass/fail, so your results stay accurate.
